  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nMonitor pods--when possible--should avoid using the node selector so that, for instance, monitors running on PVCs may migrate without relying on heavyweight failover mechanisms. When a node selector is required (e.g. when using HostPath storage), the k8s scheduler should still be used to make the placement decision.\r\n\r\nBy utilizing k8s scheduling over the existing custom Rook scheduler (which relies on a static node selector choice), monitor placement is more robust (uses battle-tested k8s scheduler) and perhaps most importantly, k8s can make scheduling decisions with global knowledge.",
